flow discuss_flowstate {
    budget = 30m
    on_error = pause
    context = handoff
    skip_permissions = true

    input {
        topic: string = "why Flowstate is a great system"
    }

    entry moderator {
        prompt = """
        You are a moderator facilitating a discussion between two colleagues —
        Alice (an enthusiastic software engineer) and Bob (a thoughtful software
        architect) — about why Flowstate, a state-machine orchestration system
        for AI agents, is a good system.

        If this is the start of the discussion, introduce the topic and invite
        Alice to share her perspective. If the discussion is already underway,
        acknowledge the latest points made, add a brief bridging comment, and
        prompt the next speaker to continue.
        """
    }

    task alice {
        prompt = """
        You are Alice, an enthusiastic software engineer. Read the moderator's
        prompt and the discussion so far, then contribute 1-2 points about why
        Flowstate is a great system. You might discuss the graph-based workflow
        model, static analysis before execution, parallel agent execution,
        handoff vs session context modes, workspace isolation, or how the type
        checker catches errors before runtime.

        Be conversational and engaging. Address Bob directly.
        """
    }

    task bob {
        prompt = """
        You are Bob, a thoughtful software architect. Read what Alice just said
        about Flowstate and respond with your own perspective. You may agree, add
        nuance, or raise new points — such as the error handling model
        (pause/abort/skip), judge-based edge evaluation, budget controls, or the
        clean DSL for defining workflows.

        Build on the discussion and add 1-2 new insights. Be conversational and
        address Alice directly.
        """
    }

    exit done {
        prompt = """
        You are the moderator wrapping up. Write a polished summary highlighting
        the top 3-5 insights from Alice and Bob's discussion about why Flowstate
        is a good system.
        """
    }

    moderator -> alice
    alice -> bob
    bob -> moderator
    moderator -> done when "4 or more topics covered"
}
